Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0017E=CWSAK0017E: A re-download request has been made for bundle {0}, which is a UTE Bundle. UTE bundles cannot be re-downloaded.
Message.Explanation: UTE bundles cannot be re-downloaded.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why a re-download request was made for this UTE bundle.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0001E=CWSAK0001E: Cannot rename file {0} to file {1}.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot rename the downloaded bundle file.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the file is valid and is not locked.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0007E=CWSAK0007E: Cannot create the global bundle cache location: {0}
Message.Explanation: The directory specified as the global bundle cache cannot be created.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why the directory cannot be created.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0010E=CWSAK0010E: Cannot add asset list {0} for bundle {1} because the bundle does not exist in the internal cache.
Message.Explanation: An asset list property in the cache contents file does not have a corresponding bundle property.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate whether the cache contents file is corrupted.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0016E=CWSAK0016E: An internal error occured. No bundle cache location has been specified.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0006E=CWSAK0006E: Local bundle file {0} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The download process did not create the local bundle file {0}.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why the file was not created.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_DELETE_EXPANDED_DIRECTORY=CWSAK0019E: Could not delete expanded bundle directory {0}.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_EXPANDED_DIRECTORY=CWSAK0018E: Could not create expanded bundle directory {0}.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0015E=CWSAK0015E: Cannot rename file {0} to file {1}. Exception: {2}
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0005E=CWSAK0005E: Cannot download the bundle because the repository URL, the bundle name, or both are missing. Repository URL: {0} Local bundle name: {1}.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot determine which bundle is to be downloaded.
Message.UserResponse: Check that a valid repository URL and bundle name are supplied.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0014E=CWSAK0014E: The bundle cache file was not initialised.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0004E=CWSAK0004E: Cannot delete file {0}. Exception {1}
Message.Explanation: The system cannot delete the bundle file.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why the file cannot be deleted.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0013E=CWSAK0013E: Cannot create the bundle cache file {0}.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot create this internal file and its parent directory.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the system has write access to the location.

Message.MsgText: ILLEGAL_BUNDLE_VERSION=CWSAK0021E: The bundle version cannot be parsed from the combined symbolic name and version: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The symbolic name and version can be parsed in multiple ways due to the presence of excessive underscore characters.
Message.UserResponse: Simplify the bundle version by removing underscore characters.

Message.MsgText: RESOLVER_EXCEPTION_DURING_REFRESH=CWSAK0023E: Encountered ResolverException while refreshing bundle URL: {0}
Message.Explanation: Refreshing the URL of a bundle from the configured bundle repositories failed with an exception.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the bundle repositories are configured correctly.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0003E=CWSAK0003E: Cannot download the bundle with URL {0}. Exception {1}
Message.Explanation: The system cannot download the bundle that has been requested.
Message.UserResponse: Check whether the URL for the bundle is correct.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0009E=CWSAK0009E: Cannot start a new thread for bundle {0} (URL: {1}) in ThreadPool {2}. Exception: {3}
Message.Explanation: The thread pool has reached its maximum size, so no more threads can be started.
Message.UserResponse: The download of affected bundles will be reattempted the next time an asset is imported, or when the server is restarted.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LOOSE_CBA=CWSAK0020E: The loose composite bundle URL {0} is not valid.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_OBTAIN_BUNDLE_REPOSITORY_SERVICE=CWSAK0022E: Cannot obtain {0} service from the service registry.
Message.Explanation: CMSG0001
Message.UserResponse: CMSG0002

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0012E=CWSAK0012E: The bundle cache location {0} exists but it is not a valid directory.
Message.Explanation: The location of the bundle cache did not resolve to a valid directory.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the file from the file system.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0002E=CWSAK0002E: Cannot download the bundle with URL {0} because there is no file at that URL.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot find the bundle that has been requested.
Message.UserResponse: Check whether the URL for the bundle is correct.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0008E=CWSAK0008E: Cannot create the thread pool {0}.
Message.Explanation: A null thread pool was returned when creating the thread pool for downloading files to the bundle cache.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why the thread pool cannot be created.

Message.MsgText: BUNDLE_DOWNLOAD_0011E=CWSAK0011E: Cannot access the service {0} from the Service Reference {1} in the service trackers.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot obtain the service from the Service Tracker.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate why the services are not available.
